I"–<p>Firstly, read <a href="{% post_url 2016-06-26-nexus6p-rooting %}">Part 1</a> (unlocking bootloader) and <a href="{% post_url 2016-06-27-nexus6p-recovery %}">Part 2</a> (flashing custom recovery) before <strong>proceeding at your own risk</strong>.</p>

<p>1) Download <a href="http://forum.xda-developers.com/showthread.php?t=1538053">SuperSU Stable</a> or <a href="http://forum.xda-developers.com/apps/supersu/2014-09-02-supersu-v2-05-t2868133">SuperSU Beta</a> (<em>I chose beta</em>)</p>

<p>2) If you downloaded it on your computer, rembmer you can send the file via USB / ADB, like so:</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">$ adb /path/to/file.zip push /sdcard/Download/file.zip</code></p>

<p>3) Boot into recovery:</p>

<p><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">$ adb reboot recovery</code></p>

<p>4) In TWRP, tap <em>Install</em> and navigate to the SuperSU you downloaded and swpie to flash.</p>

<p>5) When prompted, <em>Wipe Dalvik / Cache</em></p>

<p>I chose to make another backup here and, once booted to a live system, send the backups to Google Drive.  That way theyâ€™re easy enough to 
access, but not hogging up space on the phone itself.  I also chose to make a backup here so that I have one of <em>completely stock system</em> and a 
<em>stock + root</em> system.</p>

<p>6) Finally, <em>reboot</em> the system.</p>

<p>Now, continue to <a href="">Part 4</a> which will quicly cover flashing ROMs (which is very similar to the steps already covered).</p>

